      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KNIGHT OF RHODES (3) sat handy but was no match for the stablemate last start when beaten 2.8L. The form out of that race at this track and trip has been very good and he should get every chance from the draw. Still a 3YO on the rise and he can get back to winning ways this time. PURE MELODY (5) finished off strongly in the Wagga Guineas last time out and has been showing good promise over shorter recently. Getting out to 2000m now looks a good move and the booking of McDougall is a good push for her chances. Wouldn't surprise to see her go to another level now. MY GREEK GOD (1) never really got into the race at Kembla first-up but looks better suited under these conditions. He jumped the $2 favourite in a similar race to this prior to the break. Carries the big weight, but is worth plenty of thought. SOUTHERN SKY (6) will appreciate this easier race today and can improve. DEVILS DAUGHTER (4) won't be far away if she runs up to her recent form.",
